{
  "video_id": "7O7BMa9XGXE",
  "title": "How America's public schools keep kids in poverty | Kandice Sumner",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12826.0,
      "end_time": 15404.0,
      "text": "I want to talk to you about my kids."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15743.0,
      "end_time": 20391.0,
      "text": "Now, I know everyone thinks that their kid is the most fantastic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 20415.0,
      "end_time": 22490.0,
      "text": "the most beautiful kid that ever lived."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 23352.0,
      "end_time": 24601.0,
      "text": "But mine really are."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 24625.0,
      "end_time": 25932.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 25956.0,
      "end_time": 28330.0,
      "text": "I have 696 kids,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 28354.0,
      "end_time": 32806.0,
      "text": "and they are the most intelligent, inventive, innovative,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 32830.0,
      "end_time": 36676.0,
      "text": "brilliant and powerful kids that you&#39;ll ever meet."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 37263.0,
      "end_time": 42860.0,
      "text": "Any student I&#39;ve had the honor of teaching in my classroom is my kid."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 42702.0,
      "end_time": 46521.0,
      "text": "However, because their \"real\" parents aren&#39;t rich"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 46545.0,
      "end_time": 49421.0,
      "text": "and, I argue, because they are mostly of color,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 49445.0,
      "end_time": 51951.0,
      "text": "they will seldom get to see in themselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 51975.0,
      "end_time": 54391.0,
      "text": "the awesomeness that I see in them."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 54839.0,
      "end_time": 57353.0,
      "text": "Because what I see in them is myself --"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 57896.0,
      "end_time": 60336.0,
      "text": "or what would have been myself."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 61645.0,
      "end_time": 64380.0,
      "text": "I am the daughter of two hardworking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 64620.00000000001,
      "end_time": 66679.0,
      "text": "college-educated, African-American parents"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 66704.0,
      "end_time": 69417.0,
      "text": "who chose careers as public servants:"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 69442.0,
      "end_time": 73530.0,
      "text": "my father, a minister; my mother, an educator."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 73780.0,
      "end_time": 76614.0,
      "text": "Wealth was never the primary ambition in our house."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 76981.0,
      "end_time": 78737.0,
      "text": "Because of this lack of wealth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 78761.0,
      "end_time": 80970.0,
      "text": "we lived in a neighborhood that lacked wealth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 80995.0,
      "end_time": 83838.0,
      "text": "and henceforth a school system that lacked wealth."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 84307.0,
      "end_time": 88147.0,
      "text": "Luckily, however, we struck the educational jackpot"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 88171.0,
      "end_time": 90542.0,
      "text": "in a voluntary desegregation program"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 90566.0,
      "end_time": 93934.0,
      "text": "that buses inner-city kids -- black and brown --"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 93958.0,
      "end_time": 96612.0,
      "text": "out to suburban schools -- rich and white."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 97288.0,
      "end_time": 101480.0,
      "text": "At five years old, I had to take an hour-long bus ride"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 101730.0,
      "end_time": 103133.0,
      "text": "to a faraway place"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 103158.0,
      "end_time": 104955.0,
      "text": "to get a better education."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 105522.0,
      "end_time": 110136.0,
      "text": "At five years old, I thought everyone had a life just like mine."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 110621.0,
      "end_time": 112651.0,
      "text": "I thought everyone went to school"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 112675.0,
      "end_time": 115330.0,
      "text": "and were the only ones using the brown crayons"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 115580.0,
      "end_time": 116726.0,
      "text": "to color in their family portraits,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 116750.0,
      "end_time": 119831.0,
      "text": "while everyone else was using the peach-colored ones."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 120559.0,
      "end_time": 124173.0,
      "text": "At five years old, I thought everyone was just like me."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 124792.0,
      "end_time": 128110.0,
      "text": "But as I got older, I started noticing things, like:"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 128948.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131510.0,
      "text": "How come my neighborhood friend don&#39;t have to wake up"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 131534.0,
      "end_time": 133720.0,
      "text": "at five o&#39;clock in the morning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 133960.0,
      "end_time": 135607.0,
      "text": "and go to a school that&#39;s an hour away?"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 136278.0,
      "end_time": 138528.0,
      "text": "How come I&#39;m learning to play the violin"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 138552.0,
      "end_time": 142260.0,
      "text": "while my neighborhood friends don&#39;t even have a music class?"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 143400.0,
      "end_time": 146584.0,
      "text": "Why were my neighborhood friends learning and reading material"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 146608.0,
      "end_time": 149360.0,
      "text": "that I had done two to three years prior?"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 149882.0,
      "end_time": 151980.0,
      "text": "See, as I got older,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 152762.0,
      "end_time": 156691.0,
      "text": "I started to have this unlawful feeling in my belly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 156715.0,
      "end_time": 160623.0,
      "text": "like I was doing something that I wasn&#39;t supposed to be doing;"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 160647.0,
      "end_time": 163358.0,
      "text": "taking something that wasn&#39;t mine;"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 163819.0,
      "end_time": 165108.0,
      "text": "receiving a gift,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 165544.0,
      "end_time": 167571.0,
      "text": "but with someone else&#39;s name on it."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 167929.0,
      "end_time": 171433.0,
      "text": "All these amazing things that I was being exposed to"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 171457.0,
      "end_time": 173155.0,
      "text": "and experiencing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 173179.0,
      "end_time": 176454.0,
      "text": "I felt I wasn&#39;t really supposed to have."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 177189.0,
      "end_time": 181215.0,
      "text": "I wasn&#39;t supposed to have a library, fully equipped athletic facilities,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 181240.0,
      "end_time": 183712.0,
      "text": "or safe fields to play in."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 184208.0,
      "end_time": 186454.0,
      "text": "I wasn&#39;t supposed to have theatre departments"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 186479.0,
      "end_time": 188844.0,
      "text": "with seasonal plays and concerts --"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 188868.0,
      "end_time": 191105.0,
      "text": "digital, visual, performing arts."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 191603.0,
      "end_time": 196259.0,
      "text": "I wasn&#39;t supposed to have fully resourced biology or chemistry labs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 196283.0,
      "end_time": 199840.0,
      "text": "school buses that brought me door-to-door,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 199109.0,
      "end_time": 201537.0,
      "text": "freshly prepared school lunches"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 201561.0,
      "end_time": 203305.0,
      "text": "or even air conditioning."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 204127.0,
      "end_time": 206570.0,
      "text": "These are things my kids don&#39;t get."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 206661.0,
      "end_time": 208198.0,
      "text": "You see, as I got older,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 208222.0,
      "end_time": 211239.0,
      "text": "while I was grateful for this amazing opportunity"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 211263.0,
      "end_time": 212909.0,
      "text": "that I was being given,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 212933.0,
      "end_time": 215661.0,
      "text": "there was this ever-present pang of:"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 216210.0,
      "end_time": 218629.0,
      "text": "But what about everyone else?"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 219137.0,
      "end_time": 222507.0,
      "text": "There are thousands of other kids just like me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 222531.0,
      "end_time": 224267.0,
      "text": "who deserve this, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 224291.0,
      "end_time": 226429.0,
      "text": "Why doesn&#39;t everyone get this?"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 226453.0,
      "end_time": 230793.0,
      "text": "Why is a high-quality education only exclusive to the rich?"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 231634.0,
      "end_time": 235197.0,
      "text": "It was like I had some sort of survivor&#39;s remorse."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 235222.0,
      "end_time": 237954.0,
      "text": "All of my neighborhood friends were experiencing"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 237978.0,
      "end_time": 239803.0,
      "text": "an educational train wreck"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 239827.0,
      "end_time": 243516.0,
      "text": "that I was saved from through a bus ride."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 244670.0,
      "end_time": 246561.0,
      "text": "I was like an educational Moses screaming,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 246585.0,
      "end_time": 248194.0,
      "text": "\"Let my people go ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 248218.0,
      "end_time": 250540.0,
      "text": "to high-quality schools!\""
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 250790.0,
      "end_time": 251496.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 251520.0,
      "end_time": 256790.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d seen firsthand how the other half was being treated and educated."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 256103.0,
      "end_time": 259430.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d seen the educational promised land,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 259670.00000000003,
      "end_time": 263306.0,
      "text": "and I could not for the life of me justify the disparity."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 265550.0,
      "end_time": 270292.0,
      "text": "I now teach in the very same school system from which I sought refuge."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 270870.0,
      "end_time": 275407.0,
      "text": "I know firsthand the tools that were given to me as a student,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 275431.0,
      "end_time": 279354.0,
      "text": "and now as a teacher, I don&#39;t have access to those same tools"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 279378.0,
      "end_time": 280942.0,
      "text": "to give my students."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 281451.0,
      "end_time": 286260.0,
      "text": "There have been countless nights when I&#39;ve cried in frustration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 286500.0,
      "end_time": 287326.0,
      "text": "anger"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 287350.0,
      "end_time": 288741.0,
      "text": "and sorrow,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 288765.0,
      "end_time": 292560.0,
      "text": "because I can&#39;t teach my kids the way that I was taught,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 292581.0,
      "end_time": 296772.0,
      "text": "because I don&#39;t have access to the same resources or tools"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 296796.0,
      "end_time": 298686.0,
      "text": "that were used to teach me."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 299393.0,
      "end_time": 301563.0,
      "text": "My kids deserve so much better."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 302270.0,
      "end_time": 305133.0,
      "text": "We sit and we keep banging our heads against this term:"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 305157.0,
      "end_time": 307722.0,
      "text": "\"Achievement gap, achievement gap!\""
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 308462.0,
      "end_time": 311394.0,
      "text": "Is it really that hard to understand"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 311418.0,
      "end_time": 314643.0,
      "text": "why these kids perform well and these kids don&#39;t?"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 314667.0,
      "end_time": 316920.0,
      "text": "I mean, really."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 316664.0,
      "end_time": 318931.0,
      "text": "I think we&#39;ve got it all wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 318955.0,
      "end_time": 320116.0,
      "text": "I think we,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 320140.0,
      "end_time": 322222.0,
      "text": "as Gloria Ladson-Billings says,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 322246.0,
      "end_time": 326988.0,
      "text": "should flip our paradigm and our language and call it what it really is."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 327516.0,
      "end_time": 329135.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not an achievement gap;"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 329878.0,
      "end_time": 331806.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s an education debt,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 332417.0,
      "end_time": 337695.0,
      "text": "for all of the foregone schooling resources that were never invested"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 337719.0,
      "end_time": 341564.0,
      "text": "in the education of the black and brown child over time."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 342820.0,
      "end_time": 345846.0,
      "text": "A little-known secret in American history"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 345870.0,
      "end_time": 350923.0,
      "text": "is that the only American institution created specifically for people of color"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 351714.0,
      "end_time": 353280.0,
      "text": "is the American slave trade --"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 353866.0,
      "end_time": 355815.0,
      "text": "and some would argue the prison system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 355839.0,
      "end_time": 358650.0,
      "text": "but that&#39;s another topic for another TED Talk."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 358890.0,
      "end_time": 359239.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 359654.0,
      "end_time": 363947.0,
      "text": "The public school system of this country was built, bought and paid for"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 363971.0,
      "end_time": 368258.0,
      "text": "using commerce generated from the slave trade and slave labor."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 368651.0,
      "end_time": 372614.0,
      "text": "While African-Americans were enslaved and prohibited from schooling,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 372638.0,
      "end_time": 375796.0,
      "text": "their labor established the very institution"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 375821.0,
      "end_time": 377509.0,
      "text": "from which they were excluded."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 378420.0,
      "end_time": 383121.0,
      "text": "Ever since then, every court case, educational policy, reform,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 383145.0,
      "end_time": 386399.0,
      "text": "has been an attempt to retrofit the design,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 386423.0,
      "end_time": 389830.0,
      "text": "rather than just stopping and acknowledging:"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 389107.0,
      "end_time": 391715.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ve had it all wrong from the beginning."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 393243.0,
      "end_time": 397286.0,
      "text": "An oversimplification of American educational history."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 397310.0,
      "end_time": 398822.0,
      "text": "All right, just bear with me."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 399681.0,
      "end_time": 402758.0,
      "text": "Blacks were kept out -- you know, the whole slavery thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 403256.0,
      "end_time": 405332.0,
      "text": "With the help of philanthropic white people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 405357.0,
      "end_time": 406911.0,
      "text": "they built their own schools."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 406935.0,
      "end_time": 409269.0,
      "text": "Separate but equal was OK."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 409729.0,
      "end_time": 412459.0,
      "text": "But while we all know things were indeed separate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 412483.0,
      "end_time": 414139.0,
      "text": "they were in no ways equal."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 414571.0,
      "end_time": 419736.0,
      "text": "Enter Brown v. the Board of Education of Topeka, Kansas in 1954;"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 419760.0,
      "end_time": 422991.0,
      "text": "legal separation of the races is now illegal."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 423900.0,
      "end_time": 430128.0,
      "text": "But very few people pay attention to all of the court cases since then,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 430153.0,
      "end_time": 435426.0,
      "text": "that have undone the educational promised land for every child"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 435450.0,
      "end_time": 438414.0,
      "text": "that Brown v. Board intended."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 438438.0,
      "end_time": 442156.0,
      "text": "Some argue that today our schools are now more segregated"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 442180.0,
      "end_time": 446916.0,
      "text": "than they ever were before we tried to desegregate them in the first place."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 447963.0,
      "end_time": 451556.0,
      "text": "Teaching my kids about desegregation, the Little Rock Nine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 451580.0,
      "end_time": 452883.0,
      "text": "the Civil Rights Movement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 452907.0,
      "end_time": 456236.0,
      "text": "is a real awkward moment in my classroom,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 456261.0,
      "end_time": 458962.0,
      "text": "when I have to hear the voice of a child ask,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 459940.0,
      "end_time": 463243.0,
      "text": "\"If schools were desegregated in 1954,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 463267.0,
      "end_time": 465564.0,
      "text": "how come there are no white kids here?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 465588.0,
      "end_time": 467480.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 467720.0,
      "end_time": 468428.0,
      "text": "These kids aren&#39;t dumb."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 469292.0,
      "end_time": 471150.0,
      "text": "They know exactly what&#39;s happening,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 471542.0,
      "end_time": 472888.0,
      "text": "and what&#39;s not."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 473526.0,
      "end_time": 475760.0,
      "text": "They know that when it comes to schooling,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 476670.0,
      "end_time": 478260.0,
      "text": "black lives don&#39;t matter"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 479810.0,
      "end_time": 480493.0,
      "text": "and they never have."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 482316.0,
      "end_time": 488830.0,
      "text": "For years, I tried desperately to cultivate in my kids a love of reading."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 489416.0,
      "end_time": 492280.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d amassed a modest classroom library"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 492304.0,
      "end_time": 495601.0,
      "text": "of books I&#39;d accumulated from secondhand shops,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 495625.0,
      "end_time": 498880.0,
      "text": "thrift stores, attics -- you know."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 498112.0,
      "end_time": 500572.0,
      "text": "But whenever I said those dreadful words,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 500596.0,
      "end_time": 502792.0,
      "text": "\"Take out a book and read,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 502816.0,
      "end_time": 505248.0,
      "text": "you&#39;d think I&#39;d just declared war."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 505273.0,
      "end_time": 506966.0,
      "text": "It was torture."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 507693.0,
      "end_time": 508857.0,
      "text": "One day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 509184.0,
      "end_time": 512314.0,
      "text": "after I&#39;d heard about this website called DonorsChoose,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 512337.0,
      "end_time": 514654.0,
      "text": "where classroom teachers create wish lists"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 514678.0,
      "end_time": 516782.0,
      "text": "of items they need for their classroom"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 516806.00000000006,
      "end_time": 519333.00000000006,
      "text": "and anonymous donors fulfill them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 519357.0,
      "end_time": 523357.0,
      "text": "I figured I&#39;d go out on a limb and just make a wish list"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 523381.0,
      "end_time": 526594.0,
      "text": "of the teenager&#39;s dream library."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 527698.0,
      "end_time": 531890.0,
      "text": "Over 200 brand-new books were sent to my room piece by piece."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 532672.0,
      "end_time": 537245.0,
      "text": "Every day there were new deliveries and my kids would exclaim with glee,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 537269.0,
      "end_time": 539226.0,
      "text": "\"This feels like Christmas!\""
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 539250.0,
      "end_time": 540330.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 540354.0,
      "end_time": 541519.0,
      "text": "Then they&#39;d say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 541543.0,
      "end_time": 544415.0,
      "text": "\"Ms. Sumner, where did these books come from?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 544439.0,
      "end_time": 545655.0,
      "text": "And then I&#39;d reply,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 545679.0,
      "end_time": 549655.0,
      "text": "\"Strangers from all over the country wanted you to have these.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 550274.0,
      "end_time": 552951.0,
      "text": "And then they&#39;d say, almost suspiciously,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 554474.0,
      "end_time": 556201.0,
      "text": "\"But they&#39;re brand-new.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 556225.0,
      "end_time": 557227.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 557251.0,
      "end_time": 558829.0,
      "text": "To which I&#39;d reply,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 558854.0,
      "end_time": 560634.0,
      "text": "\"You deserve brand-new books.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 562137.0,
      "end_time": 565560.0,
      "text": "The whole experience hit home for me when one of my girls,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 565584.0,
      "end_time": 568654.0,
      "text": "as she peeled open a crisp paperback said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 569582.0,
      "end_time": 573960.0,
      "text": "\"Ms. Sumner -- you know, I figured you bought these books,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 573984.0,
      "end_time": 576722.0,
      "text": "&#39;cause you teachers are always buying us stuff."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 577158.0,
      "end_time": 581187.0,
      "text": "But to know that a stranger, someone I don&#39;t even know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 581211.0,
      "end_time": 582910.0,
      "text": "cares this much about me"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 583480.0,
      "end_time": 584935.0,
      "text": "is pretty cool.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 585870.0,
      "end_time": 588495.0,
      "text": "Knowing that strangers will take care of you"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 588519.0,
      "end_time": 590545.0,
      "text": "is a privilege my kids aren&#39;t afforded."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 592342.0,
      "end_time": 593784.0,
      "text": "Ever since the donation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 593808.0,
      "end_time": 597665.0,
      "text": "there has been a steady stream of kids signing out books to take home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 597690.0,
      "end_time": 600350.0,
      "text": "and then returning them with the exclamation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 600374.0,
      "end_time": 601962.0,
      "text": "\"This one was good!\""
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 601986.0,
      "end_time": 603340.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 603580.0,
      "end_time": 605360.0,
      "text": "Now when I say, \"Take out a book and read,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 605384.0,
      "end_time": 607603.0,
      "text": "kids rush to my library."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 608849.0,
      "end_time": 610896.0,
      "text": "It wasn&#39;t that they didn&#39;t want to read,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 610920.0,
      "end_time": 615469.0,
      "text": "but instead, they&#39;d gladly read if the resources were there."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 617579.0,
      "end_time": 619231.0,
      "text": "Institutionally speaking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 619255.0,
      "end_time": 623607.0,
      "text": "our public school system has never done right by the black and brown child."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 624680.0,
      "end_time": 626616.0,
      "text": "We keep focusing on the end results"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 626640.0,
      "end_time": 628500.0,
      "text": "or test results,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 628290.0,
      "end_time": 629875.0,
      "text": "and getting frustrated."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 629899.0,
      "end_time": 632360.0,
      "text": "We get to a catastrophe and we wonder,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 632600.0,
      "end_time": 634896.0,
      "text": "\"How did it get so bad? How did we get here?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 635890.0,
      "end_time": 637450.0,
      "text": "Really?"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 637439.0,
      "end_time": 639514.0,
      "text": "If you neglect a child long enough,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 639538.0,
      "end_time": 642628.0,
      "text": "you no longer have the right to be surprised"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 642652.0,
      "end_time": 644483.0,
      "text": "when things don&#39;t turn out well."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 645319.0,
      "end_time": 647530.0,
      "text": "Stop being perplexed"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 647770.0,
      "end_time": 648703.0,
      "text": "or confused"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 648727.0,
      "end_time": 650203.0,
      "text": "or befuddled"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 650680.0,
      "end_time": 652606.0,
      "text": "by the achievement gap,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 652630.0,
      "end_time": 653853.0,
      "text": "the income gap,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 653877.0,
      "end_time": 655496.0,
      "text": "the incarceration rates,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 655520.0,
      "end_time": 660567.0,
      "text": "or whatever socioeconomic disparity is the new \"it\" term for the moment."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 661248.0,
      "end_time": 663690.0,
      "text": "The problems we have as a country"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 663714.0,
      "end_time": 665797.0,
      "text": "are the problems we created as a country."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 666740.0,
      "end_time": 670278.0,
      "text": "The quality of your education is directly proportionate"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 670302.0,
      "end_time": 672160.0,
      "text": "to your access to college,"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 672184.0,
      "end_time": 673911.0,
      "text": "your access to jobs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 673936.0,
      "end_time": 675644.0,
      "text": "your access to the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 677594.0,
      "end_time": 682864.0,
      "text": "Until we live in a world where every kid can get a high-quality education"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 682888.0,
      "end_time": 684424.0,
      "text": "no matter where they live,"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 684448.0,
      "end_time": 686328.0,
      "text": "or the color of their skin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 686352.0,
      "end_time": 690411.0,
      "text": "there are things we can do on a macro level."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 691389.0,
      "end_time": 694953.0,
      "text": "School funding should not be decided by property taxes"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 694977.0,
      "end_time": 697208.0,
      "text": "or some funky economic equation"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 697232.0,
      "end_time": 700267.0,
      "text": "where rich kids continue to benefit from state aid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 700292.0,
      "end_time": 704377.0,
      "text": "while poor kids are continuously having food and resources"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 704401.0,
      "end_time": 705993.0,
      "text": "taken from their mouths."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 706750.0,
      "end_time": 710511.0,
      "text": "Governors, senators, mayors, city council members --"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 710535.0,
      "end_time": 713399.0,
      "text": "if we&#39;re going to call public education public education,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 713423.0,
      "end_time": 715600.0,
      "text": "then it should be just that."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 715555.0,
      "end_time": 718537.0,
      "text": "Otherwise, we should call it what it really is:"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 718562.0,
      "end_time": 720127.0,
      "text": "poverty insurance."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 721211.0,
      "end_time": 722653.0,
      "text": "\"Public education:"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 722677.0,
      "end_time": 725765.0,
      "text": "keeping poor kids poor since 1954.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 725789.0,
      "end_time": 727241.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 728733.0,
      "end_time": 733830.0,
      "text": "If we really, as a country, believe that education is the \"great equalizer,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 733855.0,
      "end_time": 737686.0,
      "text": "then it should be just that: equal and equitable."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 738158.0,
      "end_time": 742501.0,
      "text": "Until then, there&#39;s no democracy in our democratic education."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 743493.0,
      "end_time": 745000.0,
      "text": "On a mezzo level:"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 745640.0,
      "end_time": 748842.0,
      "text": "historically speaking, the education of the black and brown child"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 748866.0,
      "end_time": 752337.0,
      "text": "has always depended on the philanthropy of others."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 752361.0,
      "end_time": 755155.0,
      "text": "And unfortunately, today it still does."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 755770.0,
      "end_time": 760135.0,
      "text": "If your son or daughter or niece or nephew or neighbor"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 760159.0,
      "end_time": 761722.0,
      "text": "or little Timmy down the street"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 762253.0,
      "end_time": 764556.0,
      "text": "goes to an affluent school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 764580.0,
      "end_time": 767754.0,
      "text": "challenge your school committee to adopt an impoverished school"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 767778.0,
      "end_time": 769817.0,
      "text": "or an impoverished classroom."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 769841.0,
      "end_time": 773238.0,
      "text": "Close the divide by engaging in communication"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 773262.0,
      "end_time": 775459.0,
      "text": "and relationships that matter."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 776500.0,
      "end_time": 778300.0,
      "text": "When resources are shared,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 778280.0,
      "end_time": 779720.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re not divided;"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 779744.0,
      "end_time": 781201.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re multiplied."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 781871.0,
      "end_time": 783710.0,
      "text": "And on a micro level:"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 783734.0,
      "end_time": 785554.0,
      "text": "if you&#39;re a human being,"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 785985.0,
      "end_time": 787151.0,
      "text": "donate."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 787524.0,
      "end_time": 791587.0,
      "text": "Time, money, resources, opportunities --"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 791611.0,
      "end_time": 793974.0,
      "text": "whatever is in your heart."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 794847.0,
      "end_time": 797500.0,
      "text": "There are websites like DonorsChoose"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 797750.0,
      "end_time": 799129.0,
      "text": "that recognize the disparity"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 799153.0,
      "end_time": 801648.0,
      "text": "and actually want to do something about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 803748.0,
      "end_time": 805952.0,
      "text": "What is a carpenter with no tools?"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 806350.0,
      "end_time": 808672.0,
      "text": "What is an actress with no stage?"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 808990.0,
      "end_time": 811447.0,
      "text": "What is a scientist with no laboratory?"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 811859.0,
      "end_time": 814586.0,
      "text": "What is a doctor with no equipment?"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 815270.0,
      "end_time": 816515.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ll tell you:"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 816970.0,
      "end_time": 818434.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re my kids."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 819219.0,
      "end_time": 821350.0,
      "text": "Shouldn&#39;t they be your kids, too?"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 821893.0,
      "end_time": 823440.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 823680.0,
      "end_time": 829273.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}